      },
      "date": "2011-06-17 08:43:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThis patch is based on LU-255, but also enables the 64bit feature by default if the LUN is larger than 2^32 blocks to avoid the user having to specify extra formatting options.\n\nI need to port the 64bit change to master as well, to make the two versions more similar.\n\nIt contains limited changes to the default OST inode ratio in LU-255 to avoid creating huge numbers of inodes on large OSTs, but does not push the default OST inode ratio all the way to 1MB nor does it contain the change to the default MDT inode ratio. I wasn't sure whether we wanted to change this in 1.8.6 also.  A separate patch will contain those changes.\n\nOn a sparse loopback 32TB LV it used the following options:\n\nmke2fs -j -b 4096 -L lustre-OSTffff  -J size=400 -I 256 -i 262144 -O extents,uninit_bg,dir_nlink,huge_file,64bit,flex_bg -G 256 -E lazy_journal_init -F /dev/vgsparse/lvtest 858980352",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
